      "message": "I\u0027d recommend to include nano seconds, using the format \"20060102-150405.000000000\", and remove rand.Int(). I don\u0027t think it produces conflict practically speaking.\nIf you use rand.Int(), you should set rand.Seed before calling it. Otherwise the Seed is always 1, and the series of rand.Int()s are deterministic. http://go/godoc/math/rand/#Seed\nExample in math/rand recommends using time.Now().UnixNano() for seed, but then why not use it directly.",
